              },
              "free_text": [
                " REACTOR NEUTRONS, FLUX 6 10**12 N/CM2/SEC, FOR",
                " ONE WEEK."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".EQUIVALENT FISSION NEUTRON SPECTRUM, USING",
                " THE NI-57 AND CO-58 ACTIVITIES FROM A NI-58 SAMPLE",
                " AND MN-54 FROM THE MN-55(N,2N) REACTION",
                " AS MONITOR. THE FAST FLUX WAS ALSO CHECKED WITH",
                " AL-27(N,A) ( WITH NA-24 BURN-UP CORRECTION)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".RHODIUM SPONGE, FROM JOHNSON MATTHEY, IN AN ALUMINIUM",
                " BOX. THE IRRADIATED RHODIUM WAS SEPERATED  AFTER",
                " IRRADIATION BY VOLATISATION IN POTASSIUM BISULPHATE",
                " FUSION, THE REDUCED BY MAGNESIUM TURNINGS.",
                " A RHODIUM-IRIDIUM SEPERATION WITH CALOMEL WAS DONE",
                " TWICE, AND AG-110M WAS ALSO CHEMICALLY SEPERATED."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " ACTIVATION."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CALIBRATED GE(LI) DETECTOR. AS RH-102 DECAYS",
                " BY ELECTRON CAPTURE ONLY, ANIHILATION GAMMAS WERE",
                " COUNTED ASSUMING A QUANTUM EFFICIENCY OF 14.1 PERCENT"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
